d stimulus generation (`stimulus_gen` instantiation) remain identical to the golden testbench, only enhanced with the new display logic.\n\n**Advice to Avoid Syntax Errors:**\n1.  **Module/Port Consistency:** Always ensure the module name and port list in the DUT declaration exactly match what is expected by the testbench instantiation.\n2.  **SystemVerilog Typing:** When dealing with complex data structures (like `struct`), ensure all members are declared with explicit types (`logic`, `int`, `time'time`).\n3.  **Procedural Block Context:** Be careful when performing assignments inside `always` blocks. If you are logging values, use direct assignments (`mismatch_details.signal = signal_value;`) rather than trying to assign to struct members as if they were modules or processes.\n4.  **Finalization:** Ensure the final display logic (the timeout block) perfectly matches the requested string format.\n\n",
